		}
	}

Run the code from your main method and change the grade parameter. After you do
this, you may be wondering what the difference is between the if else and the if
condition we looked at previously.

The difference is that the if statement either executes or does not depending on
the condition. Whereas, the if else condition must execute one of the two
possible branches. i.e. it must print one of the two strings inside the if else
